### Conversation APIs - REST Client Testing
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Setup: Create test users and get tokens
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register User 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "AlicePass123",
  "confirmPassword": "AlicePass123"
}

### Login User 1 (save token as @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "AlicePass123"
}

### Register User 2 (save this ID in @otherUserId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Smith",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "BobPass123",
  "confirmPassword": "BobPass123"
}

### Register User 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Charlie Davis",
  "email": "charlie@example.com",
  "password": "CharliePass123",
  "confirmPassword": "CharliePass123"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. GET ALL CONVERSATIONS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all conversations (empty at start)
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all conversations (after creating some)
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. CREATE CONVERSATIONS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Create conversation with Bob
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012"
}

### Create conversation with Charlie
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439013"
}

### Create conversation again (should return existing, status 200)
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. GET CONVERSATION DETAILS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get conversation details (replace ID with real conversation ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/507f1f77bcf86cd799439014
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### ERROR CASES & VALIDATION
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Create conversation without otherUserId
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
}

### Create conversation with invalid user ID format
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "invalid-id"
}

### Create conversation with non-existent user
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "000000000000000000000000"
}

### Create conversation with self
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "CURRENT_USER_ID_HERE"
}

### Get conversation with invalid ID format
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/invalid-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get conversation with non-existent ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/000000000000000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get conversation (unauthorized - not participant)
### First create conversation with friend, then try accessing with different user
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/507f1f77bcf86cd799439014
Authorization: Bearer DIFFERENT_USER_TOKEN_HERE

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTHENTICATION ERRORS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### No authorization header
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations

### Invalid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-here

### Expired token (after manually setting old token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.invalid.signature

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CONVERSATION WORKFLOW
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Get current user's conversations
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2. Start new conversation with a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "NEW_USER_ID"
}

### 3. Get that conversation details
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/RETURNED_CONVERSATION_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Later: Create conversation again (idempotent - returns same conversation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "SAME_USER_ID"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### NOTES FOR TESTING
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### 1. Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token from login response
###    Steps:
###    a. Run login request
###    b. Copy token from response data.token
###    c. Set @token = <copied_token>
###
### 2. Replace user IDs with actual MongoDB ObjectIds from your database
###    - Get from create response or search users endpoint
###    - Format: 24-character hex string (e.g., 507f1f77bcf86cd799439012)
###
### 3. Test Behaviors:
###    - POST endpoint returns 201 for new conversation
###    - POST endpoint returns 200 for existing conversation
###    - POST is idempotent (calling twice returns same conversation)
###    - GET returns 200 only if user is participant (403 if not)
###    - Lists are sorted by updatedAt (newest first)
###
### 4. Expected Response Format:
###    {
###      "success": true/false,
###      "data": { /* response data */ },
###      "message": "Success or error message",
###      "statusCode": 200/201/400/403/404
###    }
###
### 5. Conversation Object Fields:
###    - _id: conversation ID
###    - otherUser: conversation partner details (in list & create)
###    - participants: both users (in detail endpoint)
###    - lastMessage: most recent message with sender info (or null)
###    - unreadCount: unread messages for current user
###    - updatedAt: last activity timestamp
###    - createdAt: conversation creation timestamp
###
### 6. Test with Multiple Users:
###    - Create conversations between different user pairs
###    - Switch tokens to verify access control (403 for non-participants)
###    - Verify unreadCount is independent per user
###
